Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.35,0:00:02.52,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这里是梵蒂冈城
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.35,0:00:02.52,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This is the Vatican City.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:09.00,0:00:11.96,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,教宗的所在地与天主教会的总部
Dialogue: 1,0:00:09.00,0:00:11.96,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Home to the Pope and headquarters of the Catholic Church.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:11.96,0:00:17.59,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,对许多人来说，这里是圣洁无瑕之地，充满了祈祷与华美的教堂
Dialogue: 1,0:00:11.96,0:00:17.59,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,To many, it's a holy and innocent place, filled with prayers and beautiful churches.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:17.59,0:00:20.44,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但如果我告诉你，在这光鲜外表之下
Dialogue: 1,0:00:17.59,0:00:20.44,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,However, what if I told you that alongside this, 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:20.44,0:00:23.83,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这座城市还藏着更为隐秘的一面呢？
Dialogue: 1,0:00:20.44,0:00:23.83,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the city has a much more covert side?
Dialogue: 2,0:00:23.83,0:00:29.51,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,你看，梵蒂冈虽是世上最小的国家，其影响力却绝非如此
Dialogue: 1,0:00:23.83,0:00:29.51,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,See, while the Vatican is the smallest country on earth, its influence is anything but.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:29.51,0:00:34.87,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它有时被戏称为“地球上最高效的情报机构”
Dialogue: 1,0:00:29.51,0:00:34.87,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It's sometimes jokingly referred to as the most effective intelligence agency on earth.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:34.87,0:00:39.82,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不，这并非指他们像中情局或军情六处那样运作
Dialogue: 1,0:00:34.87,0:00:39.82,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And no, not in the sense that they operate like the CIA or MI6, 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:39.82,0:00:42.35,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而是以一种截然不同的方式
Dialogue: 1,0:00:39.82,0:00:42.35,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,but rather in a much different way.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:42.35,0:00:46.75,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我知道这听起来很疯狂，但千真万确，而且这还不是全部
Dialogue: 1,0:00:42.35,0:00:46.75,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I know it sounds crazy, but it's true, and that's not even everything.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:46.75,0:00:52.68,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但要理解梵蒂冈情报运作的范畴，我们需要追溯其源起之时
Dialogue: 1,0:00:46.75,0:00:52.68,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But to understand the scope of how Vatican intelligence operates, we need to go back to when it first began.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:52.68,0:00:56.59,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,其渊源至少可追溯至十六世纪
Dialogue: 1,0:00:52.68,0:00:56.59,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Its origins can be traced back to at least the 16th century,
Dialogue: 2,0:00:56.59,0:00:59.52,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当时天主教会正与新教英格兰发生冲突
Dialogue: 1,0:00:56.59,0:00:59.52,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,when the Catholic Church was clashing with Protestant England.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:59.52,0:01:02.58,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,尤其是与女王伊丽莎白一世
Dialogue: 1,0:00:59.52,0:01:02.58,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And more particularly, Queen Elizabeth I.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:02.58,0:01:06.22,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,那时，欧洲因宗教改革而四分五裂
Dialogue: 1,0:01:02.58,0:01:06.22,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,At the time, Europe was divided by the Reformation.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:06.22,0:01:11.22,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,伊丽莎白治下的英格兰已脱离罗马，并皈依了新教
Dialogue: 1,0:01:06.22,0:01:11.22,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,England, under Elizabeth, had broken away from Rome and embraced Protestantism.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:11.22,0:01:13.67,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,对梵蒂冈而言，这不仅是异端邪说
Dialogue: 1,0:01:11.22,0:01:13.67,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,For the Vatican, this wasn't just heresy.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:13.67,0:01:16.74,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,更是一种政治上与生存上的威胁
Dialogue: 1,0:01:13.67,0:01:16.74,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It was a political and existential threat.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:16.74,0:01:21.80,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,时任教宗庇护五世在1570年正式将她逐出教会
Dialogue: 1,0:01:16.74,0:01:21.80,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,When then-Pope Pius V formally excommunicated her in 1570, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:21.80,0:01:25.36,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但这还不够，并认定若要对抗女王
Dialogue: 1,0:01:21.80,0:01:25.36,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,it wasn't enough and decided that if they were to counter the Queen,
Dialogue: 2,0:01:25.36,0:01:30.59,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们就需要情报来支持伊丽莎白的天主教对手，苏格兰女王玛丽
Dialogue: 1,0:01:25.36,0:01:30.59,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,they'd need intelligence to support Mary, Queen of Scots, Elizabeth's Catholic rival.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:30.59,0:01:34.49,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,因此根据研究，教宗监督建立了一个隐秘的
Dialogue: 1,0:01:30.59,0:01:34.49,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,So according to research, the Pope oversaw the creation of a covert, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:34.49,0:01:40.13,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,非正式的网络，用以监视英国宫廷并汇报其在欧洲各地的活动
Dialogue: 1,0:01:34.49,0:01:40.13,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,informal network that could monitor the English court and report on its activities across Europe.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:40.13,0:01:44.02,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,遗憾的是，关于那之后的事情信息寥寥无几
Dialogue: 1,0:01:40.13,0:01:44.02,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, there isn't much information on what came after that.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:44.02,0:01:46.19,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,至少在接下来的几个世纪里是如此
Dialogue: 1,0:01:44.02,0:01:46.19,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,At least for the next few centuries.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:46.19,0:01:52.18,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,直到1909年，教宗庇护十世的得力助手翁贝托·贝尼尼
Dialogue: 1,0:01:46.19,0:01:52.18,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It was only in 1909, when Umberto Benigni, the right-hand man of Pope Pius X,
Dialogue: 2,0:01:52.18,0:01:56.08,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,建立了一个新的间谍网络，名为“虔诚会”
Dialogue: 1,0:01:52.18,0:01:56.08,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,set up a new network of spying, called Sodalitium Pianum,
Dialogue: 2,0:01:56.08,0:02:00.35,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,梵蒂冈才在情报世界中扮演日益核心的角色
Dialogue: 1,0:01:56.08,0:02:00.35,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,that the Vatican would assume an increasingly central role in the world of intelligence.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:00.74,0:02:05.46,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这个组织诨名为“萨皮涅尔”，是一个内部间谍网络
Dialogue: 1,0:02:00.74,0:02:05.46,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Informally known as La Sapiniere, this was an internal spy network.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:05.46,0:02:08.74,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,其目标是打击教会内部的现代主义
Dialogue: 1,0:02:05.46,0:02:08.74,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Its goals were to combat modernism inside the church.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:08.74,0:02:15.85,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而我所说的现代主义，是指自由神学、圣经批判、世俗哲学之类的思想
Dialogue: 1,0:02:08.74,0:02:15.85,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And by modernism, I mean liberal theology, criticism of the Bible, secular philosophy, things like that.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:15.85,0:02:19.58,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,萨皮涅尔的运作方式基本上就像一个秘密警察机构
Dialogue: 1,0:02:15.85,0:02:19.58,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,How La Sapiniere operated was basically like a secret police.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:19.58,0:02:22.90,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,其核心圈子不超过五十名神职人员
Dialogue: 1,0:02:19.58,0:02:22.90,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,There was an inner circle of no more than 50 clergy.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:22.90,0:02:28.01,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但他们培养了一个更广泛的网络，由神父、修生和神学家组成
Dialogue: 1,0:02:22.90,0:02:28.01,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But they cultivated a much wider network of priests, seminarians and theologians
Dialogue: 2,0:02:28.01,0:02:33.70,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这些人会监视教会内任何他们认为对其保守意识形态构成威胁的人
Dialogue: 1,0:02:28.01,0:02:33.70,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,who'd run surveillance on anyone within the church they thought were a threat to its conservative ideology.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:33.70,0:02:39.34,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这意味着拦截私人信件、检查书店记录以查看谁在买什么书
Dialogue: 1,0:02:33.70,0:02:39.34,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This meant intercepting private mail, examining the records of bookshops to see who was buying what,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:39.34,0:02:41.92,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,跟踪嫌疑人等等
Dialogue: 1,0:02:39.34,0:02:41.92,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,following suspects around and more.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:41.92,0:02:46.37,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然后他们会向贝尼尼提交报告，再由他转呈梵蒂冈
Dialogue: 1,0:02:41.92,0:02:46.37,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They'd then submit reports to Benigni, who forwarded them to the Vatican.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:46.37,0:02:49.51,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这种通讯包含密码和化名
Dialogue: 1,0:02:46.37,0:02:49.51,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This communication included secret codes and pseudonyms,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:49.51,0:02:53.35,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,例如教宗庇护十世被称为“米其林夫人”
Dialogue: 1,0:02:49.51,0:02:53.35,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,such as Pope Pius X being referred to as Lady Michelin,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:53.35,0:02:58.51,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而梵蒂冈国务卿，梅里·德尔瓦尔枢机则被称为“罗密小姐”
Dialogue: 1,0:02:53.35,0:02:58.51,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and the Vatican Secretary of State, Cardinal Merry Del Valle, as Miss Romy.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:58.51,0:03:02.64,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,如果有人被认定有罪，他们的职业生涯基本上就算毁了
Dialogue: 1,0:02:58.51,0:03:02.64,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,If someone was found guilty, they could basically have their career ruined.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:02.64,0:03:06.57,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,被调查的人中甚至包括后来的教皇若望二十三世
Dialogue: 1,0:03:02.64,0:03:06.57,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,One of the people being investigated was even Pope John XXIII, 
Dialogue: 2,0:03:06.57,0:03:08.94,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当时他还是一位教会史教师
Dialogue: 1,0:03:06.57,0:03:08.94,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,back when he was a teacher of church history.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:08.94,0:03:11.70,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但可以肯定的是，他没有被进一步追究
Dialogue: 1,0:03:08.94,0:03:11.70,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But it's safe to say he wasn't pursued further.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:11.70,0:03:17.30,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,据说萨皮涅尔于1921年被教皇本笃十五世解散
Dialogue: 1,0:03:11.70,0:03:17.30,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,La Sapiniere was said to have been dissolved in 1921 by Pope Benedict XV,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:17.30,0:03:22.53,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但也有人说，它至少部分存在至第二次世界大战初期
Dialogue: 1,0:03:17.30,0:03:22.53,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,though according to others, it existed at least partly until the beginning of World War II.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:22.53,0:03:26.95,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不过说到战争，正是在此时梵蒂冈从拥有秘密警察
Dialogue: 1,0:03:22.53,0:03:26.95,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But speaking of the war, this is when the Vatican shifted from having a secret police
Dialogue: 2,0:03:26.95,0:03:29.28,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,转变为全球情报的掮客
Dialogue: 1,0:03:26.95,0:03:29.28,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,to becoming a global intelligence broker.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:29.28,0:03:30.61,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,且听我解释
Dialogue: 1,0:03:29.28,0:03:30.61,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Let me explain.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:30.61,0:03:35.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,早在1929年，梵蒂冈城通过与意大利王国签署《拉特兰条约》
Dialogue: 1,0:03:30.61,0:03:35.54,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Back in 1929, the Vatican City became an independent state inside Rome,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:35.54,0:03:40.07,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,成为了罗马城内的一个独立国家
Dialogue: 1,0:03:35.54,0:03:40.07,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,with the signing of the Lateran Treaty between them and the Kingdom of Italy.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:40.07,0:03:44.58,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但该条约也要求他们在所有国际事务中保持中立
Dialogue: 1,0:03:40.07,0:03:44.58,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But what it also did was require them to be neutral in all international affairs,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:44.58,0:03:46.44,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,除非被请求不这样做
Dialogue: 1,0:03:44.58,0:03:46.44,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,unless requested not to be.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:46.44,0:03:51.95,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,身处这样的位置，尤其是在1943年罗马被德国占领期间
Dialogue: 1,0:03:46.44,0:03:51.95,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,By being in this position, especially during when Rome was under German occupation in 1943,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:51.95,0:03:55.88,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,使其成为少数几个能让外交官、情报机构
Dialogue: 1,0:03:51.95,0:03:55.88,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,made it one of the few places where diplomats, intelligence agencies,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:55.88,0:03:58.97,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,和各地神职人员秘密会面的地方之一
Dialogue: 1,0:03:55.88,0:03:58.97,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and clerics from all over could secretly meet.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:58.97,0:04:03.22,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,结果，梵蒂冈就成了一个全球情报的掮客
Dialogue: 1,0:03:58.97,0:04:03.22,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,As a result, the Vatican became like a global intelligence broker.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:03.22,0:04:07.22,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,例如，教宗的私人秘书，罗伯特·莱伯神父
Dialogue: 1,0:04:03.22,0:04:07.22,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,For example, the Pope's private secretary, Father Robert Leiber,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:07.22,0:04:11.27,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,在庇护十二世与德国抵抗运动之间担任中间人
Dialogue: 1,0:04:07.22,0:04:11.27,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,acted as the intermediary between Pius XII and the German resistance
Dialogue: 2,0:04:11.27,0:04:16.00,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,为当时计划于1940年发动的针对德国政府的政变做准备
Dialogue: 1,0:04:11.27,0:04:16.00,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,in the lead up to a then planned coup against the German government in 1940.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:16.00,0:04:19.70,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,教宗会先审阅情报，然后再传递给英国
Dialogue: 1,0:04:16.00,0:04:19.70,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The Pope would then review the intelligence before passing it on to Britain.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:19.70,0:04:24.27,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他还就德军计划入侵低地三国向同盟国发出警告
Dialogue: 1,0:04:19.70,0:04:24.27,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,He also warned the Allies about the planned invasion of the Benelux countries.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:24.27,0:04:28.50,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,对德国人来说，他们将教宗的行为等同于间谍活动
Dialogue: 1,0:04:24.27,0:04:28.50,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,To the Germans, they regarded the Pope's behavior as equivalent to espionage
Dialogue: 2,0:04:28.50,0:04:30.16,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,并对这座城市进行监视
Dialogue: 1,0:04:28.50,0:04:30.16,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and surveilled the city.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:30.16,0:04:33.08,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,战争结束，我们进入冷战年代后
Dialogue: 1,0:04:30.16,0:04:33.08,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Once the war ended and we got into the Cold War decades,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:33.08,0:04:36.90,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,梵蒂冈的秘密行动也在此期间达到了顶峰
Dialogue: 1,0:04:33.08,0:04:36.90,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,that's where the Vatican reached the peak of their co-vote operations.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:36.90,0:04:40.50,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,你看，梵蒂冈认为共产主义本质上是无神论的
Dialogue: 1,0:04:36.90,0:04:40.50,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,See, the Vatican saw communism as atheistic in nature,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:40.50,0:04:42.59,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,说实话，通常确实如此
Dialogue: 1,0:04:40.50,0:04:42.59,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,which is usually true to be fair.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:42.59,0:04:45.78,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,所以这意味着他们从一开始就坚决反对它
Dialogue: 1,0:04:42.59,0:04:45.78,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,So it meant they were firmly opposed to it from the very beginning.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:45.78,0:04:51.66,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们对抗东方集团的策略最初围绕罗马一所名为“Russicum”的学校展开
Dialogue: 1,0:04:45.78,0:04:51.66,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Their strategy to oppose the Eastern Bloc was first centered around a school in Rome known as Russicum.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:51.66,0:04:56.42,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这所学校实际上成立于1929年，旨在为派往俄国服务的神父做准备
Dialogue: 1,0:04:51.66,0:04:56.42,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This was actually established in 1929 to prepare priests for service in Russia.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:56.42,0:04:59.46,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但数十年后，它承担了全新的重要使命
Dialogue: 1,0:04:56.42,0:04:59.46,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But it took on a whole new importance decades later,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:59.46,0:05:03.99,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,为那些能尝试潜入铁幕后执行秘密任务的神职人员做准备
Dialogue: 1,0:04:59.46,0:05:03.99,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,preparing clergy who could attempt clandestine missions behind the Iron Curtain.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:03.99,0:05:08.61,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,对于像波兰或匈牙利这样已有稳固天主教基础的国家
Dialogue: 1,0:05:03.99,0:05:08.61,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,For countries with an already established Catholic presence, such as Poland or Hungary,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:08.61,0:05:13.87,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,目标是支持当地教会的领导层，并鼓励抵抗国家控制
Dialogue: 1,0:05:08.61,0:05:13.87,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the goal was to support the church's local hierarchy and encourage resistance to state control.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:13.87,0:05:17.46,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但在天主教几乎被赶尽杀绝的苏联
Dialogue: 1,0:05:13.87,0:05:17.46,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But in the Soviet Union, where Catholicism was nearly wiped out,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:17.46,0:05:19.45,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,则是一个完全不同的挑战
Dialogue: 1,0:05:17.46,0:05:19.45,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,it was a whole different challenge.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:19.45,0:05:22.29,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这里的目标仅仅是让天主教信仰存活下去
Dialogue: 1,0:05:19.45,0:05:22.29,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The goal here was just to keep Catholicism alive.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:22.29,0:05:25.80,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,神父们以虚假身份和背景偷运入境
Dialogue: 1,0:05:22.29,0:05:25.80,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Priests were smuggled in under false identities and backstories.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:25.80,0:05:27.92,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,弥撒在地下举行
Dialogue: 1,0:05:25.80,0:05:27.92,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Mass was performed underground.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:27.92,0:05:32.10,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,关于政治氛围的报告被秘密地传送回罗马
Dialogue: 1,0:05:27.92,0:05:32.10,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And reports of the political atmosphere were secretly funneled back to Rome.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:32.10,0:05:36.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,正是因此，根据克格勃叛逃者瓦西里·米特罗欣的说法
Dialogue: 1,0:05:32.10,0:05:36.54,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It was for this reason that, according to KGB defector, Vasili Mitrokhin,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:36.54,0:05:41.85,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,克格勃将梵蒂冈视为其在海外最主要的颠覆性对手之一
Dialogue: 1,0:05:36.54,0:05:41.85,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the KGB viewed the Vatican as one of their primary subversive opponents abroad.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:41.85,0:05:45.68,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然而，当我们接近冷战末期时，事情变得更加有趣
Dialogue: 1,0:05:41.85,0:05:45.68,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Things got more interesting though when we get towards the end of the Cold War,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:45.68,0:05:48.59,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,尤其是在教皇若望·保禄二世时期
Dialogue: 1,0:05:45.68,0:05:48.59,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,especially during the time of Pope John Paul II,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:48.59,0:05:51.94,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他是近五百年来第一位非意大利籍教皇
Dialogue: 1,0:05:48.59,0:05:51.94,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the first non-Italian pope in almost 500 years,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:51.94,0:05:55.62,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,也是一位从内部洞悉东方集团的波兰人
Dialogue: 1,0:05:51.94,0:05:55.62,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and a Polish man who knew the Eastern Bloc from the inside out.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:55.62,0:06:00.90,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他在颠覆欧洲共产主义和帮助结束冷战中的作用怎么强调都不过分
Dialogue: 1,0:05:55.62,0:06:00.90,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,His role in toppling European communism and helping end the Cold War cannot be overstated.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:00.90,0:06:03.29,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,最好的例子就是波兰
Dialogue: 1,0:06:00.90,0:06:03.29,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The best example of this was with Poland.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:03.29,0:06:07.94,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,早在1979年，他首次以教宗身份返回他的祖国
Dialogue: 1,0:06:03.29,0:06:07.94,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Back in 1979, the pope made his first papal return to his home country,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:07.94,0:06:10.74,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当时有超过一千三百万人前来瞻仰他
Dialogue: 1,0:06:07.94,0:06:10.74,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,where over 13 million people came to see him.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:10.74,0:06:14.36,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,正是通过这次标志性的访问，波兰人不再恐惧
Dialogue: 1,0:06:10.74,0:06:14.36,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It was through this iconic visit that Poles stopped being afraid,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:14.36,0:06:16.49,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,反而备受鼓舞
Dialogue: 1,0:06:14.36,0:06:16.49,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and became inspired instead.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:16.49,0:06:19.58,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,由此诞生了“团结工会”运动
Dialogue: 1,0:06:16.49,0:06:19.58,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It was from this that the birth of the Solidarity Movement,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:19.58,0:06:23.52,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,一个广泛的反共社会运动和工会组织
Dialogue: 1,0:06:19.58,0:06:23.52,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,a broad anti-communist social movement and trade union, was formed.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:23.52,0:06:28.30,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,正如该运动的领导者及最终的总统莱赫·瓦文萨所说，没有他
Dialogue: 1,0:06:23.52,0:06:28.30,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Without him, as the leader of the movement and eventual president Lech Wałęsa put it,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:28.30,0:06:30.32,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这一切都不可能实现
Dialogue: 1,0:06:28.30,0:06:30.32,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,it wouldn't have been possible.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:30.32,0:06:32.02,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但这仅仅是个开始
Dialogue: 1,0:06:30.32,0:06:32.02,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But this was just the beginning.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:32.02,0:06:34.44,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,1981年12月13日
Dialogue: 1,0:06:32.02,0:06:34.44,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,On December 13th, 1981,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:34.44,0:06:38.96,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,波兰政府宣布戒严，试图对抗日益壮大的运动
Dialogue: 1,0:06:34.44,0:06:38.96,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the Polish government declared martial law in an attempt to counter the growing movement.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:38.96,0:06:43.97,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这导致梵蒂冈与中情局联手，以推翻共产主义政府
Dialogue: 1,0:06:38.96,0:06:43.97,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This led to the Vatican teaming up with the CIA to bring down the communist government.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:43.97,0:06:47.00,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这么说很疯狂，但请听我解释
Dialogue: 1,0:06:43.97,0:06:47.00,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It's a crazy thing to say, but let me explain.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:47.00,0:06:52.76,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不过首先，我想提一下，黄金和白银在2025年迎来了爆发性的一年
Dialogue: 1,0:06:47.00,0:06:52.76,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But first, I want to mention that gold and silver are having a breakout year in 2025,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.00,0:06:52.76,Yahei-1920x1080,atg3,0,0,0,,前方广告，请空降8:50
Dialogue: 2,0:08:50.65,0:08:54.36,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,言归正传，梵蒂冈与中情局合作的原因如下
Dialogue: 1,0:08:50.65,0:08:54.36,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Anyways, this is why the Vatican teamed up with the CIA.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:54.36,0:08:59.57,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,美国出于地缘政治原因反对共产主义，而教会则是出于精神原因
Dialogue: 1,0:08:54.36,0:08:59.57,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The US opposed communism for geopolitical reasons, and the church for spiritual ones.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:59.57,0:09:03.36,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但俗话说，敌人的敌人就是朋友
Dialogue: 1,0:08:59.57,0:09:03.36,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But as the saying goes, the enemy of my enemy is my friend.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:03.36,0:09:06.52,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,教皇与总统在八十年代期间会晤了四次
Dialogue: 1,0:09:03.36,0:09:06.52,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The Pope and president met four times throughout the 80s,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:06.52,0:09:09.72,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而此前的总统没有一位超过一次
Dialogue: 1,0:09:06.52,0:09:09.72,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,while no previous president had done so more than once.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:09.72,0:09:14.25,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,从第一次会晤开始，谈话就围绕着波兰和东欧展开
Dialogue: 1,0:09:09.72,0:09:14.25,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,From the very first meeting, the talk centered around Poland and Eastern Europe.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:14.25,0:09:17.38,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们知道这一点，因为里根图书馆有所提及
Dialogue: 1,0:09:14.25,0:09:17.38,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,We know this because the Reagan Library mentions it.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:17.38,0:09:21.22,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但在表面之下，他们其实有着更深层的关系
Dialogue: 1,0:09:17.38,0:09:21.22,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But beneath the surface, they actually had a much deeper relationship.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:21.22,0:09:27.79,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,前中情局副局长弗农·沃尔特斯在八十年代期间拜访了教皇近十二次
Dialogue: 1,0:09:21.22,0:09:27.79,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The former deputy director of the CIA, Vernon Walters, visited the Pope almost a dozen times in the 80s,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:27.79,0:09:33.66,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,根据前美国驻教廷大使威廉·A·威尔逊的说法——他充当了他们之间的联络人
Dialogue: 1,0:09:27.79,0:09:33.66,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,acting as their liaison, according to the former US ambassador to the Holy See, William A. Wilson.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:33.66,0:09:40.60,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们协调了联合行动，中情局为团结工会运动提供了价值数百万美元的秘密援助
Dialogue: 1,0:09:33.66,0:09:40.60,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They coordinated joint operations, where the CIA would fund millions of dollars worth of covert aid to the Solidarity Movement,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:40.60,0:09:45.05,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,从印刷机和通讯设备，到支持罢工的现金
Dialogue: 1,0:09:40.60,0:09:45.05,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,from printing presses and communications equipment, to cash to support the strikes.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:45.05,0:09:48.69,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,据著名的水门事件记者卡尔·伯恩斯坦透露
Dialogue: 1,0:09:45.05,0:09:48.69,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They were then smuggled into Poland via clergy and agents, 
Dialogue: 2,0:09:48.69,0:09:52.36,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这些物资随后通过神职人员和特工被偷运到波兰
Dialogue: 1,0:09:48.69,0:09:52.36,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,according to the famous Watergate journalist Karl Bernstein.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:52.36,0:09:57.29,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,此时梵蒂冈的对外情报机构甚至有了一个诨名
Dialogue: 1,0:09:52.36,0:09:57.29,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,There was even an unofficial name for the foreign intelligence agency of the Vatican at this point.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:57.29,0:09:58.69,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“实体”
Dialogue: 1,0:09:57.29,0:09:58.69,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The Entity.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:58.69,0:10:02.02,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,虽然这显然未经证实，但已有相关书籍问世
Dialogue: 1,0:09:58.69,0:10:02.02,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,While it's obviously unconfirmed, there's been books written about it,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:02.02,0:10:07.39,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而路易吉·波吉枢机，有时被称为“教皇的间谍”，据说曾掌管该机构
Dialogue: 1,0:10:02.02,0:10:07.39,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and Cardinal Luigi Poggi, sometimes called the Pope's spy, was said to have run it.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:07.39,0:10:11.10,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,同时，在情报方面，两国共享信息
Dialogue: 1,0:10:07.39,0:10:11.10,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, on the intel side, the two countries shared information.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:11.10,0:10:14.60,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,时任国务卿亚历山大·黑格甚至说
Dialogue: 1,0:10:11.10,0:10:14.60,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,With then-Secretary of State Alexander Haig even saying that,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:14.60,0:10:18.78,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,梵蒂冈的情报“绝对比我们的更好、更快”
Dialogue: 1,0:10:14.60,0:10:18.78,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the Vatican's information was absolutely better and quicker than ours.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:18.78,0:10:24.48,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,最终，梵蒂冈与中情局在八十年代维持团结工会运动生存的联盟
Dialogue: 1,0:10:18.78,0:10:24.48,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Eventually, the Vatican and CIA alliance of keeping the Solidarity Movement alive during the 1980s
Dialogue: 2,0:10:24.48,0:10:28.19,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,导致了波兰人民共和国于1989年垮台
Dialogue: 1,0:10:24.48,0:10:28.19,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,led to the collapse of the Polish People's Republic in 1989,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:28.19,0:10:30.60,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,以及随后波兰第三共和国的崛起
Dialogue: 1,0:10:28.19,0:10:30.60,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and the rise of the Third Republic of Poland,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:30.60,0:10:35.22,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,团结工会在几十年来首次的半自由选举中获得了权力
Dialogue: 1,0:10:30.60,0:10:35.22,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,where Solidarity gained power in the first semi-free elections in decades.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:35.22,0:10:38.42,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它的突破在东欧引发了多米诺骨牌效应
Dialogue: 1,0:10:35.22,0:10:38.42,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Its breakthrough set off a domino effect across Eastern Europe,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:38.42,0:10:41.73,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,一个又一个共产主义政权开始相继倒台
Dialogue: 1,0:10:38.42,0:10:41.73,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,as one communist regime began to fall after the other.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:41.73,0:10:44.97,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“这堪称有史以来最伟大的秘密结盟之一”
Dialogue: 1,0:10:41.73,0:10:44.97,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This was one of the greatest secret alliances of all time,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:44.97,0:10:49.04,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,里根的首位国家安全顾问理查德·艾伦如是说
Dialogue: 1,0:10:44.97,0:10:49.04,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,according to Reagan's first national security adviser, Richard Allen.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:49.04,0:10:53.24,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,同样值得注意的是，我提到的所有这些关键政府人物
Dialogue: 1,0:10:49.04,0:10:53.24,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It's important to also note that all these key administration people I've mentioned,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:53.24,0:10:58.50,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,威尔逊、黑格、沃尔特斯、艾伦，甚至当时的中情局局长威廉·凯西
Dialogue: 1,0:10:53.24,0:10:58.50,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Wilson, Haig, Walters, Allen, and even then-CIA director William Casey,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:58.50,0:11:00.62,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,都是虔诚的罗马天主教徒
Dialogue: 1,0:10:58.50,0:11:00.62,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,were all devout Roman Catholics.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:00.62,0:11:04.41,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们将美梵关系视为一个“神圣同盟”
Dialogue: 1,0:11:00.62,0:11:04.41,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They regarded the US-Vatican relationship as a holy alliance.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:04.41,0:11:09.66,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,中情局因此甚至曾经有个绰号叫“天主教情报局”
Dialogue: 1,0:11:04.41,0:11:09.66,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The CIA even used to have the nickname the Catholic Intelligence Agency for this reason.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:09.66,0:11:15.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,冷战结束后，坦白说，描述梵蒂冈情报的来源变得稀少得多
Dialogue: 1,0:11:09.66,0:11:15.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,After the Cold War ended, sources describing Vatican intelligence became much scarcer, to be honest.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:15.12,0:11:16.68,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但仍有其存在的迹象
Dialogue: 1,0:11:15.12,0:11:16.68,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But there were still signs of it.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:16.68,0:11:23.50,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,例如，1997年，比利时议会将“主业会”列入危险宗教派别名单
Dialogue: 1,0:11:16.68,0:11:23.50,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,For example, in 1997, the Belgian parliament replaced Opus Dei on a list of dangerous religious sects,
Dialogue: 2,0:11:23.50,0:11:27.72,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但之后在全球面临巨大争议，并未采纳该提议
Dialogue: 1,0:11:23.50,0:11:27.72,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,but afterwards faced major backlash worldwide and didn't adopt it.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:27.72,0:11:31.81,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,背景介绍一下，“主业会”，于1929年在西班牙成立
Dialogue: 1,0:11:27.72,0:11:31.81,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The Opus Dei, for context, was founded in Spain in 1929,
Dialogue: 2,0:11:31.81,0:11:35.65,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,其使命是帮助普通人在日常生活中找到上帝
Dialogue: 1,0:11:31.81,0:11:35.65,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,with a mission to help ordinary people find God in their daily life.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:35.65,0:11:40.56,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但在1982年，它获得了“属人监督团”的独特地位
Dialogue: 1,0:11:35.65,0:11:40.56,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But in 1982, it received the unique status of a personal prelature,
Dialogue: 2,0:11:40.56,0:11:45.42,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这意味着它只对教皇负责，可以独立于地方主教运作
Dialogue: 1,0:11:40.56,0:11:45.42,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,meaning that it answered only to the Pope and could operate independently of local bishops.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:45.42,0:11:50.67,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这为其提供了一个全球性的自主运作框架，在教会历史上极为罕见
Dialogue: 1,0:11:45.42,0:11:50.67,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This gave it a global framework for autonomous operation, rarely granted in church history.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:50.67,0:11:52.72,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,关于它的阴谋论层出不穷
Dialogue: 1,0:11:50.67,0:11:52.72,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,There have been many conspiracies about it, 
Dialogue: 2,0:11:52.72,0:11:56.49,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,从支持拉丁美洲到西班牙的独裁统治不一而足
Dialogue: 1,0:11:52.72,0:11:56.49,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,ranging from supporting dictatorships in Latin America to Spain.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:56.49,0:12:00.02,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它还是一个极其神秘的组织，这也无甚帮助
Dialogue: 1,0:11:56.49,0:12:00.02,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It doesn't help either that it's an extremely secretive organization,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:00.02,0:12:03.64,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,其成员甚至不会公开自己是其中一员
Dialogue: 1,0:12:00.02,0:12:03.64,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,where its members literally don't identify themselves as being part of.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:03.64,0:12:07.79,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但这些阴谋论是真是假，还是纯属夸大，都难以判断
Dialogue: 1,0:12:03.64,0:12:07.79,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But whether the conspiracies are true or just exaggeration is hard to tell.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:07.79,0:12:10.35,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但我猜想，真相至少介于两者之间
Dialogue: 1,0:12:07.79,0:12:10.35,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But I'd assume it's at least somewhere in the middle.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:10.35,0:12:12.07,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,用托马斯·图罗夫斯基的话来说——
Dialogue: 1,0:12:10.35,0:12:12.07,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,In the words of Thomas Turovsky, 
Dialogue: 2,0:12:12.07,0:12:16.36,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他是一名波兰共产主义情报官员，曾作为间谍渗透梵蒂冈
Dialogue: 1,0:12:12.07,0:12:16.36,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,a Polish communist intelligence officer who infiltrated the Vatican as a spy,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:16.36,0:12:19.06,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,后来最终成为派驻该国的外交官
Dialogue: 1,0:12:16.36,0:12:19.06,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,before eventually becoming a diplomat to the country,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:19.06,0:12:22.75,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“梵蒂冈的间谍比《007》里的还多”
Dialogue: 1,0:12:19.06,0:12:22.75,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,there were more spies in the Vatican than in James Bond films.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:22.75,0:12:26.26,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,梵蒂冈的间谍活动有许多不为人知之处是必然的
Dialogue: 1,0:12:22.75,0:12:26.26,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It's inevitable that much about the Vatican's spycraft is unknown,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:26.26,0:12:28.56,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而且很多将永远是个谜
Dialogue: 1,0:12:26.26,0:12:28.56,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and much will forever remain so.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:28.56,0:12:33.47,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但可以肯定的是，每隔几个月就会有惊人的内幕被曝光
Dialogue: 1,0:12:28.56,0:12:33.47,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But there are some crazy revelations being brought to light every few months, that's for sure.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:33.47,0:12:38.70,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当然，梵蒂冈不仅是进行间谍活动的一方，它也是间谍活动的目标
Dialogue: 1,0:12:33.47,0:12:38.70,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Of course though, the Vatican isn't just the one doing the spying, it's also the target of it.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:38.70,0:12:44.94,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,美国，更具体地说是国家安全局，被曝出于2013年窃听了梵蒂冈的通讯
Dialogue: 1,0:12:38.70,0:12:44.94,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The US, and more specifically the NSA, were revealed to have tapped Vatican communications in 2013.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:44.94,0:12:49.92,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而在教皇选举会议期间，也就是枢机团集会选举新教皇之时
Dialogue: 1,0:12:44.94,0:12:49.92,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And during papal conclaves, which is when the College of Cardinals convenes to elect a new pope,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:49.92,0:12:52.79,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,梵蒂冈会进入全面的反情报模式
Dialogue: 1,0:12:49.92,0:12:52.79,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the Vatican goes into full counterintelligence mode.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:52.79,0:12:55.22,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,会议地点西斯廷教堂
Dialogue: 1,0:12:52.79,0:12:55.22,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The location of it, the Sistine Chapel, 
Dialogue: 2,0:12:55.22,0:12:59.46,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,会由梵蒂冈的宪兵队进行清扫，检查有无隐藏的麦克风或摄像头
Dialogue: 1,0:12:55.22,0:12:59.46,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,is swept for hidden microphones or cameras by the Vatican's Jean de Marie Corps,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:59.46,0:13:01.43,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,宪兵队也就是其安全部队
Dialogue: 1,0:12:59.46,0:13:01.43,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,which is the security force.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:01.43,0:13:06.33,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,会部署信号干扰器以阻断手机、无线网络和无线电传输
Dialogue: 1,0:13:01.43,0:13:06.33,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Signal jammers are deployed to block cell phones, Wi-Fi and radio transmissions.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:06.33,0:13:09.49,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,甚至枢机主教住所的窗户都会被封锁
Dialogue: 1,0:13:06.33,0:13:09.49,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Even the windows of the cardinal's residences are blocked.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:09.49,0:13:13.87,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然而，这并不能阻止外国情报机构试图干预
Dialogue: 1,0:13:09.49,0:13:13.87,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Yet, this doesn't stop foreign intelligence agencies from trying to interfere.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:13.87,0:13:15.67,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,赌注实在太高了
Dialogue: 1,0:13:13.87,0:13:15.67,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The stakes are simply too high.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:15.67,0:13:21.52,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,教皇的影响力如此之大，各国政府不可能不想在决定谁将赢得选举中占得先机
Dialogue: 1,0:13:15.67,0:13:21.52,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And the pope has too much influence for governments not to look for a leg up in determining who will win the election.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:21.52,0:13:25.77,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,总之，目前梵蒂冈的情报本质上就是其外交手腕
Dialogue: 1,0:13:21.52,0:13:25.77,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Anyways, for now, the Vatican's intelligence is essentially its diplomacy.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:25.77,0:13:31.77,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,与184个国家保持着外交关系，教皇使节派驻在几乎每个国家的首都
Dialogue: 1,0:13:25.77,0:13:31.77,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,With 184 states maintaining relations, papal envoys posted in nearly every capital,
Dialogue: 2,0:13:31.77,0:13:35.44,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,以及数百万散布在全球各地的神职人员和俗职人员
Dialogue: 1,0:13:31.77,0:13:35.44,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and millions of clergy and lay workers scattered across the globe,
Dialogue: 2,0:13:35.44,0:13:39.38,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们仍然能接触到可与任何政府匹敌的信息流
Dialogue: 1,0:13:35.44,0:13:39.38,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,they still have access to information flows that rival any government.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:39.38,0:13:44.97,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,从这个意义上说，梵蒂冈仍然运作着世界上最广泛的人力情报网络之一
Dialogue: 1,0:13:39.38,0:13:44.97,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,In that sense, the Vatican still operates one of the broadest human intelligence networks in the world.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:44.97,0:13:48.97,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,只是这个网络建立在教牧关系之上，而非传统的间谍
Dialogue: 1,0:13:44.97,0:13:48.97,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Just one built on pastoral ties rather than traditional spies.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:48.97,0:13:51.48,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,至少这是我们所了解的
Dialogue: 1,0:13:48.97,0:13:51.48,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,At least that's what we're aware of.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:51.48,0:13:55.90,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,感谢您的观看，别忘了关注以获取更多此类内容
Dialogue: 1,0:13:51.48,0:13:55.90,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Thank you for watching, and don't forget to subscribe for more content like this.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:55.90,0:13:57.73,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,咱们下期见
Dialogue: 1,0:13:55.90,0:13:57.73,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I'll see you in the next one.